+## Refresh procedure
+
+If Maven Central or UCAR publishes a newer version of one of the vendored
+artifacts, prefer migrating to the remote version rather than bumping the
+vendored copy:
+
+1. Remove `<repository>project.local</repository>` for that dependency in `pom.xml`.
+2. Add a regular `<dependency>` pointing to the remote version.
+3. `mvn clean verify` to confirm the build resolves.
+4. Delete the no-longer-needed JAR/POM from `java/local/`.
+5. Commit with a `build:` message.
+
+If you must keep the local repository (e.g. the artifact still isn't on Maven
+Central), add a new version alongside the old one rather than overwriting, so
+reverts are trivial.
+
+## How to add a new library
+
+Based on <https://sookocheff.com/post/java/local-maven-repository/>:
+
+```sh
+mvn deploy:deploy-file \
+  -Durl=file:${project.basedir}/java/local/ \
+  -Dfile=/path/to/your.jar \
+  -DgroupId=com.example \
+  -DartifactId=libname \
+  -Dpackaging=jar \
+  -Dversion=1.2.3
+```
 
